abstract = {Our future is certainly machine dependent, and robots will undoubtedly replace most of human work. The dream is not just an illusion but also a natural result of the two most important technologies of today: artificial intelligence (AI) and the Internet of Things (IoT). AI deals with the creation of systems that can learn to mimic human functions, using their previous experience and without any manual intervention. AI refers to analytical methods in the execution of certain tasks, which can replace human intelligence. AI helps computers to learn from experience, adapts to new inputs, and performs tasks of a human nature. From research labs to your living room, AI now lives everywhere. AI has already taken jobs from humans and will continue to do so as it becomes wider and more successful. On the other hand, the IoT is a network of various devices that are linked over the internet and that can capture and exchange data among themselves. IoT helps the devices/objects to observe, identify, and understand a situation or environment without being dependent on human assistance. From everyday objects like kitchen appliances, vehicles, thermostats, and baby monitors to everything else is connected to the Internet through embedded devices.}
